subSubSection.paragraph:
Hemispermatophore (Fig: 19-h): lamelliform (TL 3; LL 1.8; LW 
0.4 mm
); lamella simple, without distal crest; with two lobe-shaped hooks located basally, one of the hooks reduced; lamella with basal notch present near the hooks. Capsular region with mesal, median lobe present.
